snippet: Prime Minister David Cameron returned from two troubled capitals with promises of further partnerships, but there was also concern about him overextending Britain’s foreign commitments.
abstract: British Prime Min David Cameron returns from trips to Algiers and Tripoli, Libya, with promises of further partnerships in fields of defense, counterterrorism and intelligence-sharing, but some worry that he is overextending Britain's foreign commitments.
lead_paragraph: Prime Minister David Cameron returned from two troubled capitals with promises of further partnerships, but there was also concern about him overextending Britain’s foreign commitments.

headline.seo: Mixed Response in Britain to Cameron’s North Africa Trip
headline.main: Cameron Shows Grit in North Africa, but Stirs Concerns About New Entanglements
headline.print_headline: Cameron Shows Grit in North Africa, but Stirs Concerns About New Entanglements
